{
    "description_long": "This is a rectangular grave yard enclosed by a stone or concrete fence with regularly spaced posts and a lattice-like upper section. Inside the enclosure, there is a small mausoleum with a red gabled roof, arched doorway, and blue-tinted windows, positioned near one end of the yard. Scattered throughout the grassy area are several grave markers, including upright headstones and a few toppled or leaning stones. The entrance to the grave yard is marked by a double-gated stone archway, centrally located along one side of the fence. The overall scene is orderly, with the mausoleum as the focal point and the grave markers arranged in a loose pattern. The materials and design suggest a traditional, well-maintained cemetery space suitable for an urban or suburban context.",
